      "content": "Skip to content Wild Resilience at cfar Home » Visit » Wild Resilience Wild Resilience is a facilitated leadership and team experience designed to help high-performing professionals step out of constant demand and into clarity. Hosted at Central Florida Animal Reserve and guided by Dana Wells of Sunshine Coaching Group, the program uses nature as a grounding force for reflection, renewal, and forward-thinking leadership.By removing teams from screens, schedules, and daily pressure, Wild Resilience creates space for perspective, presence, and meaningful connection in an environment that naturally encourages calm focus and insight. A Leadership Reset in Nature Today’s leaders and teams operate in environments defined by speed, complexity, and continuous input. Wild Resilience offers a deliberate pause. The experience invites participants to slow down, observe, and reconnect with the qualities that support sustainable leadership, including resilience, adaptability, and creativity.Nature is not a backdrop for this work. It is an active part of the experience, providing a setting that supports awareness, curiosity, and thoughtful conversation. designed for Executive leaders guiding teams through growth, transition, or complexity Professionals working in high-pressure fields such as technology, healthcare, engineering, and innovation-driven industries Teams seeking renewed energy, stronger collaboration, and greater alignment The program is especially valuable for organizations looking to support long-term performance without burnout. The Experience Wild Resilience blends professional coaching with time spent in a natural environment that encourages reflection and connection. Participants engage in guided conversations, quiet observation, and intentional activities designed to support insight and shared understanding.Throughout the experience, teams are encouraged to step back from problem-solving mode and engage in deeper thinking that supports trust, creativity, and clarity. Outcomes Teams and leaders who participate in Wild Resilience often leave with: Improved communication and stronger working relationships Renewed focus and energy Greater flexibility in thinking and decision-making A clearer sense of purpose and shared direction Practical insights and commitments that translate back into daily work Each participant is supported in identifying how the experience connects directly to their role and responsibilities. A Collaborative Program Wild Resilience is offered through a collaboration between Sunshine Coaching Group and Central Florida Animal Reserve. Together, the program combines experienced leadership facilitation with a setting that naturally supports presence, learning, and personal growth. Visit Sunshine Coaching Group Website Wild Resilience Inquiry Form Use this form to request availability and details for your team. Full name Email Phone Message send",
