      "url": "https://cflar.dream.press/get-involved/donate",
      "title": "Donate - Central Florida Animal Reserve",
      "content": "Skip to content Support the Mission Home » Get Involved » Donate Your support helps Central Florida Animal Reserve provide long-term care, enrichment, veterinary services, and education for big cats. Every contribution directly supports daily operations and the well-being of the animal residents who call CFAR home.Giving is simple, secure, and impactful. Give Online Online giving is the fastest and most effective way to support CFAR.Donations made through the Network for Good portal are available immediately and can be applied directly to animal care, enrichment, medical needs, and facility operations. Donors may choose a one-time gift or set up a recurring monthly donation for sustained support throughout the year. Donate Monthly Giving Monthly contributions provide dependable support that allows CFAR to plan ahead and respond to ongoing needs. This option is ideal for donors who want to make a lasting impact through manageable, recurring gifts. Monthly giving options are available directly through the Network for Good portal. Give Monthly A Lasting Tribute - CFAR’s Brick Program Memories are often preserved in meaningful ways. At Central Florida Animal Reserve, many supporters feel a lasting connection to the cats, the environment, and the mission to address the challenges big cats face in the future while providing value to society today.The Brick Program offers an opportunity to create a permanent place in CFAR’s history. As the facility continues to grow, personalized bricks placed at the Welcome Center recognize individuals, families, and organizations who have contributed to the success of our mission.A brick may serve as:A memorial honoring a loved oneA tribute marking a milestoneA symbol of commitment to conservation and educationEach engraved brick becomes part of the physical foundation of CFAR, reflecting the community that sustains this work. Choose your Brick Other Ways to Give For those who prefer alternative giving methods, CFAR offers several additional options. Donate by Check Donations by check are welcome. Mailing Address: Central Florida Animal Reserve 500 Broussard Rd St. Cloud, FL 34773 Donate via PayPal PayPal donations are accepted for donors who prefer this platform. PayPal In-Kind Donations CFAR accepts select in-kind donations including materials, supplies, food items, and professional services. These contributions help offset operational costs and may be tax-deductible for businesses.To inquire about in-kind donations, contact TeamCFAR via email at give@cflar.org. Company Matching Gifts Many employers offer matching gift programs that can double the impact of your donation. Check with your employer to see if they participate. Matching gifts are a simple way to increase support for CFAR at no additional cost to you. Legacy Giving Legacy giving allows supporters to include CFAR in long-term financial plans such as wills or trusts. These gifts help ensure continued care and stewardship for future generations of animals.To learn more about legacy giving options, contact TeamCFAR via email at give@cflar.org. Additional Ways to Support CFAR Support for CFAR goes beyond individual donations. Get Involved Partnerships offer businesses and organizations opportunities to support CFAR through collaborative initiatives and shared mission alignment. Sponsorships allow companies to support events, programs, or on-site needs while gaining visibility and community engagement. Memberships provide individuals with a deeper connection to CFAR through exclusive benefits and ongoing support opportunities. Stay Connected Supporters are encouraged to stay informed about CFAR’s work, updates, and opportunities to engage. Sign Up Thank You for Supporting CFAR Every gift, whether one-time or recurring, plays a role in supporting animal care, education, and long-term stewardship at Central Florida Animal Reserve. Your generosity helps ensure that big cats receive the care and respect they deserve. Donate",
